description:
"Chipper" for time: 

100 Kettlebell swings lagom 24/16 kg or individual weights
80 Wallballls
60 Deadlifts 60/40 kg
40 Situps
20 Single arm Devils press alternating 22,5/15 kg or individual weight

Cap 15 min but if your done before 12 min continue to 15 min as a amrap

5 rounds for time
20 Wallballs 3/2,7m 9/6 kg 
5 Devils press 2 x 22,5/15 kg or individual weights
Time cap 12 min

Very intense for time met-con. Can you push on the last rounds?

B. 12 min AMRAP
6 Pullups/Band/Ring row
9 Lateral burpees over barbell/Step over
12 Front squats 30/20 kg or individual weight

B. Very intense met-con with big movements. Probably pace a little bit from the start to be able to keep the intensity all the way through.

15 min AMRAP

15 Wallballs 9/6 kg 3/2,7 m
20 KB swings Russian 32/24 kg
5 L + 5 R One arm DB hang clean and jerks 22,5/15 kg
10 Toes to bar/Knee raise 2 for 1

5 rounds for time:
5 Devils press 2 x 22,5/15 kg
7 Chest to bar pullups/Pullups
9 Burpee boxjump 60/50 cm
35 Double unders/Singel unders 2 for 1
Time cap 16 min

Scaled variation
5 rounds for time:
5 Devils press 2 x 15/10 kg
7 Band pullups/Jumping pullups
9 Burpee box step up
50 Singel unders
Time cap 16 min

High skill met-con with a lot of upper body work. Can you move well all the way through?

5 rounds (30 min total)

1 min Row
1 min Handstand hold on wall or practice free standing
1 min Fly wheel bike
1 min Turkish get up (1 left and 1 right arm) 16/12 kg or individual weight
1 min Singel unders 25s L elbow side plank + 25 s right

5 x E2M
3 Front squats starting at 70% of 1RM
directly into
3 high boxjumps

Tight set up on every Front squat and stay as upright as possible. If your leaning forward consider lowering the weight to establish best possible movement pattern.

9 x OTM
4 - 6 Ring/Bar dips with 4s eccentric
4 - 5 L + 4 - 5 R Skater squats for quality and depth
40 - 50s Farmers carry with KB or DB

 Strict and with control on the Ring/Bar dips and Skater squats.

4 x E2,5M
1 - 5 Strict Ring muscle-ups/Progression work
or 
Scaled variation
2 - 5 Supinated strict pullups/Eccentrics/Band
2 - 5 Bar dips/Eccentrics/Band

If you still haven´t got the strict muscle up practice the strength and technique on that. A good alternative is also to work on the strict strength requirements for the movement.

Red - Intense

A. 5 x E2M
4 - 1 rep Hang power clean and jerk

B. "Karen"
For time:
150 Wallballs 9/6 kg 3/2,7 m
Time cap 12 min"	"A. Start at 70% and build the weight from there. Focus on the extension and powerful hip extension on both movements. 

B. Classic benchmark with very high intensity. Be smart from the start so you don´t make to big sets. Excpect some leg soreness tomorrow...

Yellow - Intermediate

A. 4 x E3M
3 - 5 Sumo deadlift new set up on each rep
5 - 7 Ring pushups with 3 s eccentric

B. TEAM 
20 min AMRAP
60 Kettlebell swings american 24/16 kg (divide anyhow)
30 Situps synchronized
60 Squat jumps/Squats (divide anyhow)
30 DB Push jerk or Push press 22,5/15 kg (divide anyhow)

A. Tight core and make sure to anchor the hips before every rep. On the ring pushups make sure to keep the shoulders tight together with the core. 

B. Team workout with four different movements. Make sure to communicate all the way through and if one of you feels stronger he/she takes a bigger chunk.

2 Rounds (32 min)

3 min Flywheel bike
1 min Handstand hold wallfacing/Pike hold
3 min Shuttle run 10 m or Treadmill
1 min Hang from the bar. Try different grips supinated, mix grip and also small swings back and forth or sideways. 
3 min Singel unders two feet, run, one foot etc. Mix it up!
1 min Front leaning rest in the rings/Floor. Best possible hollow "gymnasty" position!
3 min Ski erg
1 min Heavy sandbag och Medball hold

Endurance session which will be strengthening the central capacity (heart and lungs) and also the muscular upper body isometric endurance. Maybe try nose breathing on the conditioning movements.

Green - Endurance

A. 16 x OTM
50s Farmers carry KB or DB
50s Front leaning rest rings/Floor
25s L + 25s R One arm overhead KB or DB carry
50s Walking lunges

B. 16 x OTM
50s 2xKB front rack carry
50s Hang from the bar or rings (different grips)
25s L + 25s R Suitcase carry KB or DB
50s Double unders/Single unders

Eight different basic movements in a endurance setting. If this is your third or fourth session this week take it a bit easy today.

4 x E3M
5 Heavy deadlifts 
directly into
8 - 10 m Heavy sled drag
B. 4 x E3M
5 Front squats with 1s hold i the bottom
directly into
3 Broad jumps with controlled landings
C. 4 x E3M
6 - 8 Lying DB bench press with 3s eccentric
directly into
10 Barbell rows with supinated grip 2s eccentric

10 - 1 reps for time:
Power clean and Jerk 50/35 kg or 60% of 1 RM
Lunge wallballs 9/6 kg 3/2,7 m
Time cap 15 min

Scaled variation
Power clean 40/25 kg
Backward lunges with WB in a overhead position
Time cap 15 min

Two big movements in a very tough combination. Probably move to singles on the PC and J early and also make sure to keep the standard when it comes to the height of the LWB throws. Two big movements in a very tough combination. Probably move to singles on the PC and J early and also make sure to keep the standard when it comes to the height of the LWB throws.

Yellow - Intermediate

A. 10 min AMRAP
30/25 cal row, bike, ski or Run 400 m
15 Wallball lunges 9/6 kg and 3/2,7 m
10 Toes to bar/Knee raises 2 for 1

At minute 12
B. 10 min AMRAP
30/25 cal Row, Bike, Ski or Run 400 m
15 DB backward lunges carry anyhow 22,5/15 kg
10 Knees to elbows on the bar/20 Situps

At minute 24
C. 10 min AMRAP
30/25 cal Row, Bike, Ski or Run 400m
15 DB step ups 60/50 cm 22,5/15 kg
10 V-ups/Tuck ups

Three ten minute amraps with a lot of cardio work. Pace and recover on the machine and maybe go unbroken on the rest. 

At Home
A. 3 sets;
15 s L-sit
10 V-ups
15 Pike-compression (1 leg raise at a time)
rest min 60 s between sets

B. Outdoor gym session
20 min amrap - Quality first!
5 strict ctb/pull up
5 deficit push ups
10 OH- lunges (single arm) with DB, KB or stone?
20 russian twist or Bicycle crunches

4 x E3,5M
1 - 5 Power snatch starting at 60% of 1 RM
1 - 4 Rope climbs optional with or without legs/Floor variation

Explosive hip knee extension and fast feet on the PS. Best possible technique on the rope climb or keep building that strength with a floor variation.

5 min AMRAP
20 One arm DB snatch 22,5/15 kg
3 Rope climbs 3,5 m
3 min Rest
5 min AMRAP
5 Devils press 2 x 22,5/15 kg
3 Bar muscle - ups/Bands/Jumping variation from box

Scaled alternative
5 min AMRAP
20 One arm DB snatch at individual weights
8 Ring rows at individual angle
3 min Rest
5 min AMRAP
5 Devils press at individual weights
8 Australian rows

Two short and technical amraps. All of the options will build your grip and pulling strength. Make sure to use the chalk and even thou the amraps are short pace it according to your capacity. On the Australian row make sure that the bar is firmly stuck to the rack for safety measures.

EMOM x 12 
1) 10-40sec Handstand Tuck Hold - Wall facing 
2) 10x L-sit leglift over Medball/DB
3) 4-10 HS Plate step ups (plates outside hands)
4) 4-8 Pull Ups in rope/Row in rope

B.  AMRAP 3x3 - 2 min rest   
5 HSPU 
6 alt V ups 
10 Airsquats

OLY
A. EMOM x 5
5 Snatch push press (behind neck)
B. EMOM x 5
5 Snatch push jerk (behind neck)
C. 10 min. Go E2M
5-4-3-2-1 Hang squat snatch
D. In 12 min. 
Build up to a heavy 1-3RM OHS

15 min AMRAP
15 Wallballs 9/6 kg 3/2,7 m
15/13 cal Row
15 Boxjumps 60/50 cm

"Recover" on the row and pace from the start to stay below the lactic thresh hold.

"Chipper" for time:
85 Wallballs 9/6 kg 3/2,7 m
65 Boxjump over 60/50 cm
45 Toes to bar
25 Power snatch 45/30 kg or 60% of 1RM
9 Wall walks
Time cap 16 min

Scaled variation
85 Wallballs 9/6/3 kg 2,7 m
65 Box step over 60/50 cm
45 Knee raises
25 Power snatch 30/20 kg
5 Wall walks or 9 Walk out to pushup
Time cap 16 min

Long "Chipper" style met-con that finishes with wall walks. Pace this one from the start to enable a strong finish. Probably break up the WBs, T2B and Power snathces in small sets.

18 min AMRAP
9 Burpee boxjumps
18 Wallballs 9/6 kg and 3/2,7 m
27 Kettlebell swings lagom 24/16 kg

Big movements so probably keep the tempo down if you want to be able to stay below the lactic thresh hold.

20 min AMRAP
20 Squats
15 Situps optional with Abmat
5 + 5 One arm DB push press 2x22,5/15 kg or individual weights
5 Devils DB power clean 2x22,5/15 kg or individual

Clean technique all the way through and find your own tempo staying just below the lactic thresh hold.

4 x EMOM
6-8 tempo push ups 21x1
10-12 Alternating v-ups
5 - 7 + 5 - 7 Skater squats for quality
rest 1 min

name: Open 20.1
description:
AMRAP in 15 minutes
3 Wall Walks
12 Dumbbell Snatches 22,5/15 kg
15 Box Jump Overs 60/50  cm

Scaled variation
AMRAP in 15 minutes
3 Partial Wall Walks or Walk out to pushup
12 Dumbbell Snatches 15/10 kg or lighter
15 Box Jump Overs 60/50 cm or lower

The exact standards can be read here; https://games.crossfit.com/workouts/open/2022/1
For training thou touching the chest or nose to the wall without arching the back is a good standard. 
Find your own sustainable pace from the start and if possible finish strong the last two minutes.

18 min AMRAP
15 Kettlebell swings american 24/16 kg
12 Burpees
9 Thrusters 30/20 kg
6 Lunge wallballs 9/6 kg 3/2,7 m

 Tricky intermediate met-con because of the big movements and a relatively large leg load. If your goal is to keep an even tempo all the way through you will probably have to pace a lot from the start.

A. 8min 
4-5 Rope climbs/ legless or practice

B. 3 rounds
5-7 Saw in rings
10-20m Sandbag walk
6-8 Ring dips 
3-6 Strict HSPU 

C. 4 rounds - 30 sec ON/ 15sec OFF
Plank diagonal lifts
Lying Windshield wipers

OLY
5xEMOM
3 Power clean and jerk
5xE2M
1 power clean
2 front squat
1 jerk
5xE3M
4 Front squat 80%
5xE2M
2 Front squat 90%

name: Handstand rock training
description:
6 times E2M - 10 Handstand rock
Good position, core tight glutes tight

4 x E3M

 5X5 Backrack backward barbell lunges 
  + 
  5 L + 5 R One leg KB deadlifts

Green - Endurance

A. 15 min AMRAP
150 Singel unders
20 Box step ups 60/50 cm (alternating leg)
25 Deadlifts 60/40 kg or 40% of 1RM

B. 15 min AMRAP
15 Kettlebell swing lagom 24/16 kg
20 Situps
25 Backward lunges

Two somewhat light aerobic met-cons but probably break up the DL´s on the second one. The pace on the Single unders is also very individual. Rest 1 minute btw A. and B.

Red - Intense

A. 5 x E2M
3 Deadlifts + 2 Hang power clean + 1 Jerk
Build up weight from 60% of 1 RM

B. "Grettel"
10 rounds for time of:
3 Power clean and jerks 60/42,5 kg or 60% of 1 RM
3 Barfacing/Lateral burpees over bar
Time cap 12 min

A. Touch and go deadlifts and an unbroken flow on the whole complex. 

B. Very intense benchmark with a spicy combination. Only resort to singles on the PC and Jerk if you need to.

Yellow - Intermediate

A. 4 x E3M
5 + 5 Backward barbell lunges
5 Bar dips 3s eccentric/Eccentric only

B. 20 min AMRAP
5 Deadlifts 100/70 kg or 60% of 1 RM
10 Pushups
15 Sit-ups
20 Squats

A. Start with your weaker leg on the Bw barbell lunges. 

B. Pace this one from the start to stay below the lactic thresh hold. The Dls should definitely be able to stay unbroken but probably break up some of the other movements.  

Solid at Home
A. 2-3 rounds:
30 alternating cossack squats
30s kneeling thoracic twist on each side
30s shoulder flexion pulses
30 s crab extension
Do this before the workout

B. 10 min amrap
200 m löpning
lateral hops x 30 (15 cm mark)
Pistols x 10
Mountain climbers x 20

1 min on, 1 min off x 3
1. Handstand hold/pike hold
2. Wall sit
3. lateral pistol hold 30/30

3 rounds of:
30 s wall sit + weight
10 squat jumps (+weight)
20 jumping lunges
rest 1-1,5 min

15 min 4 x 5 rep Back squat starting at 70% of 1 RM

Tight core, deep and with control.

In 12 min 4 - 5 sets x 5 reps
5 Back squats 
Start from 70% of 1RM and increase the weight btw 2,5 - 5 kg each set
Rest minimum 90s btw each set

A. Tight set up on each rep and brace harder as the weight increases.

600 m Row, Ski or Run
8 Top to floor Turkish get ups alternating side 16/12 kg
32 Situps
4 Wall walks or 4 Walk outs to pushup
16 DB Box step overs 60/50 cm 22,5/15 kg carry anyhow

Aerobic pace from the start and break up all the movements besides the monostructural work.

name: Randy with a twist
description:
For time:
25 Power snatch 35/25 kg or 40 - 50% of 1RM
75 Double unders/Singel unders 2 for 1
25 Power snatch 
75 Double unders/SU 2 for 1
25 Power snatch
75 Double unders/SU 2 for 1
Time cap 13 min

Very intense met-con with two classic CF movements. If 225 DU is to much maybe do a combination of DUs and Singel unders but don´t settle for the easy way out.

Yellow - Intermediate

A. 9 x OTM
5 - 8 Power clean at individual weights
6 - 15 Boxjump over 60/50 cm
4 - 8 Ring or Bar dips/4 eccentric Bar dips

B. 9 x OTM
6 - 15 Toes to bar
25 - 50 Double unders/Single unders 2 for 1
1 - 3 Wall walks/3 - 6 Walk out to pushup

C. 9 x OTM
6 - 12 DB power clean 2 x 22,5/15 kg
10 - 24 Split jumps/Backward lunges
3 - 5 Devils press 2 x 22,5/15 kg

At HOME
A. 3 rounds
2 reps short of failure: SA Row,
rest 30 s
2 reps short of failure: SA Press/side
rest 90 s

B. For time
10 Air Squats, 30 DU, 200m Run
20 Air Squats, 30 DU, 200m Run
30 Air Squats, 30 DU, 200m Run
40 Air Squats, 30 DU, 200m Run
50 Air Squats, 30 DU, 200m Run

Green - Endurance

42 min x OTM (7 rounds)
5 + 5 Skater squats for quality
10 Ring row with pause on the top for quality
8 - 16 m Bear crawl with high hips and straight legs
14 - 20 Russian KB swings with straight arms at individual weight
10 - 20s Star plank/Side plank hold
25 - 90 Singel unders

On the Skater squats keep the chest up on every rep and don´t rush the reps. 
When holding the pause on the Ring rows touch the hand on the side of the chest. 
Bear crawl for quality with high hips and as straight legs as possible. 
Tight core and shoulders on the Russian swings. Also use the breathing to create a snappy strong hip extension. 
The Star plank/Side plank can be scaled to the knee if neccessary. 
Singel unders as relaxed as possible and with different kind of jumps ie slow, fast, running, one foot etc. 

Solid at Home
5 rounds, for quality
4 V-ups
6 alternating V-ups
8 straddle V-ups
10 situps
rest as needed in between sets

5 sets of
5 – Burpees
20 – mountain climbers
20 – Jumping lunges/Backward lunges
10 – Ground to overhead/5 Burpees
rest 30s in between sets.

5 rounds of:
Core and Carry
10 m Duck walk (arms extended overhead if possible)
10 sit ups
10 m OH carry R
10 tuck - ups (touch the toes)
10 m OH -carry L
10 Elbow to knee aka Bicycle crunches
10 m Zercher carry
Find something pretty heavy

5 x E3,5M
2 - 6 Deficit handstand pushups/Mat/Abmat
1 - 2 L + 1 - 2 R Turkish get up with KB or DB 

Scaled variation
3 - 6 Pike pushups with tempo 3s down
1 - 2 + 1 - 2 Turkish get up KB or DB

Build to a to a harder HSPU on each set using plates or less abmats. On the TGUs also build up using heavier and heavier weights.

20 min AMRAP
14/12 cal Row
10L + 10R One arm DB push jerk/press 22,5/15 kg
8 DB step ups carry anyhow 60/50 cm
6 Burpee with DB power clean 2 x 22,5/15 kg

Long intermediate met-con with a lot of Dumbell work. Use the row as your recovery piece.

6 x E2M
1 - 5 Power clean and jerk
Build from 60% of 1RM. Touch and go reps with best possible technique.

4 x E2M
10 - 8 - 6 - 4 Ring pushups

Strict Ring push ups with increased load every round.

6 min AMRAP
6 Chest to bar pullups
12 Overhead squats 50/35 kg or 50 - 60% of 1 RM
3 min Rest
6 min AMRAP
12 Toes to bar
6 Squat snatch 50/35 kg or 60 - 70% of 1 RM

Scaled variation
6 min AMRAP
6 Pullups/Band/Jumping
12 Overhead squats 30/20 kg or individual weight
3 min Rest
6 min AMRAP
12 Knee raises
6 Squat snatch or Squat clean at 30/20 kg or individual weights

Tough couplet of barbell and bar work. Probably break up both movements from the start and strive for best possible movement/technique.

Activation/strength and mobility posterior chain/hamstrings
A. 20 frog pumps
20-30 s hamstring walk in/out
5 hip rolls/leg
x3

Red - Intense

A. 4 x E3,5M
3 Zombie paus squats 33x1
5 Harop curls or Leg curls on the rower with 4s eccentric

B. 5 rounds for time:
5 Thrusters 60/40 kg or 60% of 1RM
10 Power clean 
15 Handrelease pushups
Time cap 15 min

A. Use wedges under the heels or oly shoes on the Zombie squats to enable a upright sound position. A good depth is important on these ones. 

B. The thrusters should be challenging today and try to go heavier then usually if the technique feels good. 
Singels or small sets on the PC and probably break up the HR pushups from the start.

TEAM

A. STHLM 15 min Technique/Strength practice with the Worm
Deadlifts, Clean and Push press over the head (4 - 6 pers)

A. Nyköping 5 x E3M
1 round of Dumbell D.T. each
12 DB deadlifts - 9 DB hang power clean - 6 Shoulder to overhead anyhow
Choose a dumbell weight that is somewhat challenging and maybe increase the weight gradually.

B. TEAM "Kelly-ish"
5 rounds for time
400 m Run or Row
30 Boxjumps 60/50 cm
30 Kettlebell swings american 32/24 kg
Time cap 22 min

C. Partner stretch
2 rounds of
30s Each of hanging from the bar while your partner is pushing you forward in the upper back creating a stretch for the shoulders, chest and upper back arch-extension. 
90s Pancake straddle stretch pulling each other forward hooking the the hands/lower arm 45s each creating a stretch for the adductors, medial hamstrings and lower back. 

A. STHLM Communication on when to lift is everything when it comes to using the Worm. Start with getting the Dl going and the move over to Power clean and Push press over the head to the other shoulder. If there is time maybe also try walking lunges. 
NYKÖPING Unbroken sets on every complex and if the technique is sound increase the weights if possible.

B. Intense "short" Team met-con with heavy KB swings. Small sets and effective quick changes. 

C. Breath and relax into the stretch and communicate with your partner. Push on the scaps and it´s ok to have a pretty good pressure. On the Pancake stretch make sure the feet are in a good position that enables a nice feeling and stability. Be gentle on the pull and listen to your friend. 

STRENGTH
A. 4 x E3M
5 Snatch deadlift. New set up on each rep
6 Alternating DB Arnold Z press 4s eccentric
B. 4 x E3M
5 + 5 One arm DB overhead walking lunges
7 + 7 One leg 2 x DB deadlifts
C. 3 x E3M
10 - 15 Back extensions in the GHD
10 - 20s L-sit hold parallettes
10 - 20s + 10 - 20s Starplank hold

Green - Endurance

A. 16 min AMRAP
800 m Row, Ski or Run
40 Kettlebell swings american 16/12 kg
20 KB Goblet backward lunges 16/12 kg
10 Lateral burpees over KB 

Rest for 1 min btw A. and B.

B. 16 min AMRAP
800 m Row, Ski or Run
40 KB sumo deadlift high pull 24/16 kg
20 KB Goblet squats 24/16 kg
10 Burpees

Pace this one from the start hard if you want to stay in the aerobic zone. 	

Solid at Home
A. 3 rounds
10 s hollow hold
5 alligator roll
10 s arch hold
rest 1 min

B. 7-10 rounds, outdoor gym
10 pull ups/ringrodd/kroppsrodd i utegym
10 bear squats
10 stock-press/strict press
every 2,5 min; 20 jumping jacks

Green - Endurance

A. 20 min AMRAP
40 Squats
2L + 2R Turkish get ups 16/12 kg
30 Situps
4 - 2 Wall walks/4 Walk out to pushup
100 Single unders

B. 20 min AMRAP
30 Walking lunges any direction
15 Pushups
30 Kettlebell swings lagom 24/16 kg
15 Toes to bar/20 Knee raises
100 Single unders

Rest for 1 minute btw A. and B.

Aerobic pace means that you will have to break up the movments in small sets.

20 min AMRAP
6 Burpee boxjumps 60/50 cm
12 One arm DB snatches 22,5/15 kg
18 Wallballs 9/6 kg 3/2,7 m
1 min Rest

Long intermediate amrap in a interval format. If your strong on the OA DB snatch and WB´s maybe go unbroken?

15 min AMRAP
20/16 cal Row
15 Situps
10 Push press 45/30 kg or 60% of 1 RM

The sit-ups will bring the heartrate down on most of us so probably push a little bit harder then normally on the row and Push press.

6 x E2M
3 Deadlift + 2 Low hang power clean + 1 Front squat
Build up the weight gradually focusing on the technique

Start the hang power clean below the knees. Maybe go heavy if the technique feels good.

name: Filthy fifty
description:
For Time;
50 Box Jumps/Step ups 60/50 cm
50 Jumping Pull-Ups
50 Kettlebell Swings american 16/12 kg or individual weight
50 Walking Lunge Steps
50 Knees-to-Elbows/Knee-raises
50 Push Presses 20/15 kg or individual weight
50 Back Extensions in the GHD/50 Barbell goodmornings 20/15 kg
50 Wall Ball Shots 9/6 kg 3/2,7 m
50 Burpees
50 Double-Unders/Singel unders 2 for 1 Double under
Time cap 35 min

The Filthy fifty is a classic CrossFit benchmark workout that can be very hard if your going all out. If this is your first workout of many this week it´s recommended to stay back on the pace and break up or slow down on all of the movements. 

The correct height for the Jumping pull-ups is 5 to 10 cm below the wrist. 

To accommodate the workout in a class setting the movements can be performed in any order.

A. 3 x E2,5M
6 Back squats 
Starting from 75% of 1 RM

B. 3 x E2M
6 Z press with DBs

A. Brace hard on the Back squats and if possible increase the weight a bit each set.

B. Strict controlled tempo on the DB Z press

6 x E90s
1 Snatch pull + 1 Power snatch + 1 Squat snatch
Build up weight from 60% of 1 RM or Technique work 

 On the Sn pull make sure to keep the barbell close to the body, on the Power snatch make sure move the feet fast and on the Sq snatch aim for a controlled squat/receiving position on every rep.

12 x OTM
20 - 50s Wallfacing handstand hold
4 - 8 Strict straight leg toes to bar
15s L + 15s R Skater squat holds
40 - 50s Farmers carry

Best possible Handstand line, locked knees on the SSL t2b and chest up on the Skater holds.

AMRAP 25 min - outdoor session
1,5 min run
14 mountain climbers
12 upphopp/tuck jumps
10 australian/reversed row/bent over row
8 dips/pike pushups

name: Death by... burpees
description:
EMOM For as Long as Possible

1 Burpee in the first minute
2 Burpee in the second minute3 Burpee in the third minute
etc...

name: Smoked legs
description:
25 min amrap 
Broad jumps x 4
Jump squats x 4
Laterala lunges x 6 alt ben
Bear Squats x 8
Table rocks x 10
Diagonal Mountain climbers x 12
Air squats x 14
jumping lunges x 16
2 min active recovery (walk)

4 x E3M
5 Back squats Tempo 30x1
5 Harop curls/Leg curl on the rower 4s eccentric
Build the weight from 70% of 1 RM on the BS

Brace more and more as the weight gets heavier.

5 rounds for time:
6 Clusters 60/40 kg or 60 - 70% of 1 RM
9 Barfacing burpees or 12 Lateral burpees
12 Chest to bar pullups/Pullups
Time cap 15 min

Very tough and intense met-con with a lot of shoulders and legs. Probably pace the first two rounds to get a feeling of the correct tempo.

21 min AMRAP
42 Lunges walking forward in any direction 
35 Sumo Deadlift high pull 35/25 kg
28 Bicycle crunches touching elbow to knee/Without touch
21 Pushups
15 Pullups or Barbell row same weight as SDLHP

Long intermediate met-con with a lot of everything. Pace it from the beginning.

6 x E90s
1 - 3 Power snatch
Gradually increase the weight or technique work

Work on speed and technique.

5 x E3,5M
2 - 6 Deficit handstand pushups/Mat/Abmat
5 + 5 Overhead barbell split squat

Scaled variation
3 - 6 Pike pushups
5 + 5 Overhead barbell split squat (technique)

If your doing deficit HSPU start with 10kg plates and build from there. Small steps is essential. On the OH split squat make sure to keep a vertical upper body position.

5 x E2M
1 - 6 Bar muscle-ups/Progression work

Scaled variation
2 - 5 Supinated strict pullups/Eccentrics/Band
2 - 5 Bar dips/Eccentrics/Band

Use a jumping variation from a box on the B mups or work from the hang progressively higher and higher. A combination of both of them can also be used or a band variation.

12 min AMRAP ascending ladder
2 Wallballs 9/6 kg 3/2,7 m
2 x 5 m Shuttle run
4 Wallballs
4 x 5 m Shuttle run 
6 Wallballs
6 x 5 m Shuttle run
8 Wall balls
8 x 5 m and so on...

Draw a line right behind 1,5 m from the wall and the next line another 5 m back. Touch the hand on the floor on each shuttle run.

3 x 4 min AMRAP 
1 Power clean
1 Lateral Burpee
1 Pullup
2 Power cleans
2 Lateral burpees
2 Pullups
3 Power clean
3 Lateral burpees
4 Power clean
and so on...
3 min rest between each set

Threes sets of very intense work. Try to stay somewhat even when it comes to the number of reps each set and finish strong on the last one.

16 min AMRAP
40 Double unders/Single unders 2 for 1
10 Deadlifts 100/70 kg or 50% of 1 RM
8 Boxjump over 60/50 cm
